caption:
Table 1: Image Matching Challenge results. The primary metric is (mAA), the mean Average 
Accuracy in pose estimation, up to 10 o . We also report (NM) the number of matches (given to 
RANSAC for stereo, and to COLMAP for multiview). For stereo, we also report (NI) the number of 
RANSAC inliers. For multiview, we also report (NL) number of landmarks (3D points), and (TL) 
track length (observations per landmark). The top 3 results are highlighted in red, green and blue.

Table 3: Ablation: match supervision. We com-
pare mAA on the Image Matching Challenge val-
idation set, for DISK models learned with pixel-
to-pixel supervision or epipolar constraints.

Table 4: Ablation: NMS. We compare the fea-
ture selection strategy used for training (top) with 
NMS at inference time. Here we use all detected 
features, rather than subsample by score.

Table 5: Ablation: NMS vs grid size. We show 
mAA vs. grid & NMS size on IMC2020-val, 
capping the number of features to 2k.

Table 6: Image Matching Challenge: Breakdown by scene (2k features). We report results for 
each of the 9 scenes, and their average.

Table 7: Image Matching Challenge: Breakdown by scene (8k features). We report results for 
each of the 9 scenes, and their average.
